Q. What is the differance between editable and configure only interfaces?
A. In SAP Cloud Platform Integration (SAP CPI), integration packages contain artifacts (like iFlows) that can be either editable or configure-only.
ğŸ”¹ 1ï¸âƒ£ Editable Interfaces:
âœ… Allows full modification of the integration flow (iFlow).
âœ… You can add, delete, or modify components inside the iFlow.
âœ… Suitable for custom integrations that need business-specific logic.
âœ… Example: Developing a custom API to integrate SAP S/4HANA with a third-party system.
ğŸ‘‰ Use Case: When creating a completely new integration or making major customizations to an existing iFlow.

ğŸ”¹ 2ï¸âƒ£ Configure-Only Interfaces:
âœ… You can only configure predefined parameters (like endpoints, credentials, or mappings).
âœ… The internal structure of the iFlow cannot be modified.
âœ… Typically used for pre-packaged SAP content (like SuccessFactors, Ariba, and S/4HANA integrations).
âœ… Example: An SAP-delivered standard iFlow that connects SAP SuccessFactors with SAP ERP.
ğŸ‘‰ Use Case: When using SAP standard integration content and only need to modify connection parameters.
